Exxaro Resources, Life Healthcare May Move: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-06-06T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/exxaro-resources-life-healthcare-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index lost 302.12,
or 1 percent, to 31,575.65 in Johannesburg, extending its drop
in the week to 2.5 percent.  Exxaro Resources Ltd. (EXX)  : Workers at the South
African coal miner may strike after the company decided to go
ahead with a plan to fire 300 workers, a labor union said.
Exxaro shares increased 20 cents, or 0.1 percent, to 153.95
rand.  Life Healthcare Group Holdings Ltd. (LHC)  : Old Mutual
Life Assurance Company Ltd. said it reduced its holding in Life
Healthcare by 5 percent to 103 million shares, representing
about 10 percent of  voting rights  in the company. Life
Healthcare shares rose 16 cents, or 1 percent, to 16.75 rand.  The following stocks will begin trading without the right
to the latest dividends:  Atlantic Enhanced Income Fund (ATLENHA SJ), Atlantic Real
Income Fund (ATREINA SJ), Barloworld Ltd. (BAW SJ), Catalyst SA
Property Equity Fund (CATSAPA SJ), Ceramic Industries Ltd (CRM
SJ), Combined Motor Holdings Ltd (CMH SJ), Coronation Fund
Managers Ltd (CML SJ), Gold Reef Resorts Ltd (GDF SJ), MAS Plc
(MSP SJ), PSG Alphen Equity Builder Fund (PSGAEBA SJ), PSG
Alphen Income Fund of Funds (PSGGILT SJ), PSG Alphen Prudential
Fund of Funds (APPRFOF SJ), PSG Konsult Income Fund of Funds
(PSGADWI SJ), PSG Optimal Income Fund (PSGALPO SJ), PSG
Preferred Dividend Fund (PSGPREF SJ), Pick n Pay Stores Ltd (PIK
SJ), Pick’n Pay Holdings Ltd (PWK SJ), Plexus Flexible Income
Fund (PLEXFLI SJ), Pretoria Portland Cement Co. (PPC SJ), Raubex
Group Ltd (RBX SJ), SA French Ltd (SFH SJ), Spar Group Ltd. (SPP
SJ).  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 0.4 percent to $24.08.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) advanced 1 percent to $45.44. BHP
Billiton Plc (BBL US) dropped 1.5 percent to $75.60. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) declined 3.1 percent to $5. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) slid 0.9 percent to $15.90. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) rose 1.4 percent to $14.15. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) dropped 2.6 percent to $27.20. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
was unchanged at $5.33. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) declined 2.1 percent
to $51.57.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
